Lauretta Onochie, aide to President Muhammadu Buhari on new media, on Thursday mocked Nigerian politicians, Senator Dino Melaye, and Senator Shehu Sani, over their failure to secure the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) during the just concluded primaries. Recall that Sani lost the Kaduna governorship ticket to Honourable Isah Ashiru on Wednesday, while, Melaye lost the PDP Kogi West Senatorial ticket to TeeJee Yusuf. Onochie in a Twitter post on Thursday expressed happiness over their failure, wishing them a happy ‘retirement’. -Advertisement- She wrote, “Staying In Retirement. Good for Kaduna State. “Good for Kogi State. Good for Nigeria.”